.TH "ibmvmc_process_close_resp" 9 "ibmvmc_process_close_resp" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ibmvmc_process_close_resp \- Process Close Response
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" ibmvmc_process_close_resp
.BI "(struct ibmvmc_crq_msg *crq "  ","
.BI "struct crq_server_adapter *adapter "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "crq" 12
ibmvmc_crq_msg struct
.IP "adapter" 12
crq_server_adapter struct
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This command is sent by the hypervisor in response to the managemant
application Interface Close message.

If the close fails, simply reset the entire driver as the state of the VMC
must be in tough shape.
